                     <p>
                        <br>¶Estos verbos de. 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">Ti</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>Ti</caption><tr><td>ri-</td></tr><tr><td>HAB</td></tr><td colspan="1">'(habitual prefix)'</td></table></span></span>. 
                        activos 
                        no son muchos 
                        porque
                        <br>la mayor 
                        cantidad de los verbos 
                        activos 
                        de esta 
                        lengua
                        <br>está en los de. 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">to</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>to</caption><tr><td>t-</td><td>o</td></tr><tr><td>HAB</td></tr><td colspan="2">'(habitual prefix &lt;t-&gt; follwed be an &lt;o&gt;)'</td></table></span></span>. 
                        Porque así como las otras 
                        conju-<br>gaciones acuden por 
                        
                           pasivos a estos de. 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">ti</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>Ti</caption><tr><td>ri-</td></tr><tr><td>HAB</td></tr><td colspan="1">'(habitual prefix)'</td></table></span></span>, 
                        así 
                        a-<br>cuden por 
                        activos a los de 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">to</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>to</caption><tr><td>t-</td><td>o</td></tr><tr><td>HAB</td></tr><td colspan="2">'(habitual prefix &lt;t-&gt; follwed be an &lt;o&gt;)'</td></table></span></span>. 
                        Pues digamos ahora
                        <br>de estos. 
                        V.g. 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">Tilítea</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>Tilítea</caption><tr><td>ri-</td><td>líte</td><td>=a</td></tr><tr><td>HAB</td><td>lower</td><td>=1s</td></tr><td colspan="3">'I lower'</td></table></span></span>, 
                        abajar otra 
                        cosa. 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">Colítea</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>Colítea</caption><tr><td>cu-</td><td>líte</td><td>=a</td></tr><tr><td>PERF</td><td>lower</td><td>=1s</td></tr><td colspan="3">'I lowered'</td></table></span></span>. 
                        preté<br>rito. 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">Calítea</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>Calítea</caption><tr><td>ca-</td><td>líte</td><td>=a</td></tr><tr><td>IRR</td><td>lower</td><td>=1s</td></tr><td colspan="3">'I will lower'</td></table></span></span>, 
                        futuro. Plural del presente, 
                        <span class="popover-markup inline"><mark class="trigger">teliteno</mark><span class="content hide inline"><table><caption>teliteno</caption><tr><td>t-</td><td>e-</td><td>lite</td><td>=no</td></tr><tr><td>HAB</td><td>1pl</td><td>lower</td><td>=1pl</td></tr><td colspan="4">'We lower'</td></table></span></span>,
